serif:
Oh, the cactus bloomed. Hehe.
The flowers are tiny, but they're so cute.

Hmm, I have so much homework...
Then there's band practice and work too.
Seems like it's going to be a busy summer.

It's been a while since we last studied together at Saki's.
Oh... I wonder if I should bring my guitar.

Summer's a busy time!
There are festivals to go to, then there's the pool and the beach!

Summer homework?
Heh, I like to get it out of the way early so I can enjoy the holidays!
I've got to make the most of the only three summers I get as a high-schooler!

I'm a pretty good swimmer.
Saki and I used to go to the pool often.

Anyone else interested in astronomy?
The sky's crystal-clear in summer.
I should check up on Miku and Luka, and thank them for helping me out.

It's never too hot at Miku's SEKAI.
I wish we could do our rehearsals there all the time.
I don't mind just hanging out as long as we have enough time for practice.

We haven't played with sparklers since we were little...
Well, I guess you can count me in.

It's been raining a lot...
Thankfully Miku let me practice over in SEKAI where I don't have to worry about the weather!

My summer plans? Hehe...
Going swimming with Haruka and everyone!
Shaved ice specials are on the menu at my part-time job for a limited time! Check them out!

I wonder if we can practice somewhere nice and shady...
It might not be safe to practice in such intense heat.

I recommend visiting the aquarium in the summer.
There's A/C and you can see all the fishes.

Shaved ice has zero calories, right?
I mean, not counting the syrup...
No, I can't justify it like that.

Idols can't let themselves get sunburnt.
We have to take care of our complexion.

I need a new swimsuit.
Maybe this time I'll go for a bikini for a change.

Is shaved ice a Japanese thing, or is it Western?
It's delicious either way.
Some people get spicy food cravings in the summer, but that's a bit much for me...

New SPF creams come out every year.
It's hard knowing which one's best for me.

Being able to practice in SEKAI is such a help.
It's nice there, and we don't have to worry about heatstroke.

Make sure to do all your summer vacation homework, An...
H-Hey, where are you going!?
When going to the beach, I like taking photos more than actually swimming.
Our snake had a really clean shed, the skin came off all in one piece. Wanna see? No?
Even Vivid Street's emptied out because of the heat.

It's too hot, I'm dying!
Kohane, let's get some ice cream!

The back alley's haunted?
You're pulling my leg.
N-No, I'm not scared!

The summer festival's coming up!
I won't be satisfied unless I'm on stage.

Ugh, I can't take this heat...
Maybe I'll go cool off at Weekend Garage.
I like being on the soccer team, but it's tough playing outdoors in this heat.

My parents said I never used to actually get into the water at the pool.
But I think I can probably swim.
Akito thinks game arcades are too noisy, but at least they have A/C on.

Did you finish your summer homework, Akito?
You can't run from it, you know.

Ughh, it's too hot...
I can't practice...
I used to love playing with sparklers with Saki and her friends.

Emu wants a splishy-splashy show.
I mean sure, that'll keep us cool, but where does she think we'll get all the water from?
So many festival foods to choose from! Caramel apples, cotton candy, shaved ice!

Summer is a time for adventure!
Everyone who wants to join the Emu Expedition, gather ‘round!

The garden hose is your friend on hot days.
Oh look, it's Tsukasa!
Get ready to get soaked!
Can't I just stay in my room, with the A/C on full blast?
Heat's bad for robots. Robo-Nene, here's a cold wet towel for you.
Now my summer homework's done, I can play games without any distractions.
I feel like I'm going to end up baked to a crisp...
Sigh... I wonder who thought up the idea of giving out homework during summer vacations.

I'm worried about Robo-Nene.
She's getting so hot, you could fry an egg on her!
It's so unbearably hot outside that I can't force myself to leave my room...

I'm not really affected by the summer heat...
Could it be because of my healthy diet?

You know those mirages you see on roads in summer?
That's called heat haze.

Everyone else is sweating like mad.
Could it be that I'm more resilient towards changes in the weather?
I've got to keep an eye on my fish tank, so it doesn't get too hot.

How can Kanade eat hot noodles in this heat?
Maybe it's the A/C?
Oh man, why can't the school be closed on rainy days?

Keeping up to date with the latest trends in cosmetics is important.
But doing so makes me want to buy all of it!

Akito, go buy me ice cream...
Hmph, he ran off again.

The sun's really beating down today.
If I go out, I might melt...
In this kind of weather, I can already picture Ena pestering her brother to buy her ice cream or something.

Yikes, what a downpour.
I hope it doesn't rain when I go shopping for fabrics.
There's plenty of songs suitable for singing on rainy days!
Don't forget to stay hydrated on hot days, even when you're out and about!

Summer vacation, at last!
What's everyone doing this year?

Saki invited me to watch fireworks with her this summer.
I can't wait!
The girls have been coming to my world to take shelter from the rain lately.

I admire how Ichika and her friends take studying seriously.
I wish I could help.

I've started looking forward to rainy days.
That's when Minori's group comes to visit.

It would be awesome if fireworks went off during the show.
I kind of want to try it.

Rin has this idea to do a show on the beach.
I think it could be fun.

MEIKO hung a wind chime on the terrace.
Where did she find it...?
It never gets too hot in SEKAI. Poor Kohane, having to deal with the heat in hers!

Summer vacation...
That explains why Konane has been coming by so often!

Whew! Wearing a mascot costume is no joke!
It gets so hot and stuffy!

KAITO wants to light some fireworks.
Maybe we will! Heehee♪

I love summer ghost stories♪
Hmm... Wasn't there a haunted house somewhere in SEKAI?
I'm so happy my friends drop in to take a break from the hot summer in their world!

Mizuki's wind chime doesn't work...
Maybe it's because there's no wind here?

Sparklers are so pretty...!
I'd like to try them myself sometime.
I'm wild about summer fireworks, but sparklers are pretty fun, too!
I heard that eating shaved ice too fast will give you brain freeze. What's that like?
Look, Len! Don't those clouds look like delicious cotton candy?

I wanna go to festivals, and watch fireworks, and go camping!
Summer's the best!
Summer homework should be just "Have fun!" or "Learn new songs!"
Rin wants to have a sparkler party night, so we're getting stuff ready.

The weather's really hot lately.
Make sure to take good care of yourself.
I want to sing along to the sound of waves, dancing together with the sea breeze.
What I like best about summer festivals is not the food or fireworks, but the music!
Careful not to get heatstroke in summer! And always carry a bottle of water.

There's a lot of music festivals in summer!
Anyone else want to come along?

The weather's unpredictable in summer.
Watch out for sudden thunderstorms!

Combat the hot weather with... ice cream!
It's not a good idea to eat too much, though.
Just hearing the gentle sound of a wind chimes makes me feel cooler, somehow?

I'm loving this weather.
Going for a swim in a river or the ocean would feel divine!

It was around this time that year that we saw a meteor shower together.
It's kind of nostalgic...

Saki wants to do something "seasonal,"
but I'm not sure what she'd like.
Saki keeps herself warm in the winter with hats, scarves, gloves, and even thermal underwear.

It's still winter, but they're already writing about spring fashion in this magazine.
I feel like I'm gonna forget what season it is.
What's winter without snow? I want to have a snowfight and make a snowman!

We're meeting up for dinner this weekend.
Hona's making winter hotpot!

My hands are cold...
I have to warm them up before the rehearsal!
Cheese fondue is apparently a trendy winter food but I can't stand the smell...

Saki... You bundle up too much.
You'll get all sweaty and catch a chill!

I don't care if it's cold.
Don't cling to me, Shizuku!

Dry air's no good for my bass.
I'll have to oil the fret board more often.
Even in winter, you see people wearing short sleeves among the audience at outdoor gigs.

Keeping everyone's hearts warm!
I'm Minori, and I'm aiming to be the kotatsu of the idol world!
Huh? No good?

I've never done winter sports before.
I wonder if there's a skating rink nearby?

Yikes, it's freezing!
I hope Miku's okay with us rehearsing in her SEKAI...
It'd be cool to visit a zoo where you can see penguins walking on snow.

The days have gotten shorter.
We'll have to make our rehearsals more time-efficient.
It's not easy being cheerful when the weather's cold, but as an idol I want to do my best to keep on smiling.

Moisturizer's so important in winter!
Performers can't afford to have dry, flaky skin!

An idol's health is important!
Gotta be careful not to get sick and miss a show!

It's so cold, even stray cats have hidden away somewhere.
I hope they're warm.

I'm cold, Shiho. Can I snuggle up?
Hey, don't walk away from me!

Asahina does archery barefoot, even in winter!
It doesn't seem to affect her focus though.
I hate cold weather, but I do miss building snowmen with Shiho.

Eek! Static electricity's so much worse in winter.
I get a shock every time I pick up the mic.
Count Pearl's vivarium is kept warm so she doesn't hibernate.
Peach buns are so cute and tasty, but you can hardly buy them anywhere.

It always gets hot playing a show.
It makes you forget it's winter!

Brr! It's so cold, and windy to make it worse!
I'd better put on some tights.
Kohane, let's go to my cafe and warm up with some hot chocolate!
The cold dry air is rough on my throat, but I don't like wearing snoods.
It's freezing! Ena's shut-in lifestyle seems appealing at this time of year.
Outfits that look good and also keep you warm are the way to go in winter.
I'm named after winter, but I feel the chill just as much as you do.
I could really use a cup of coffee right about now.

Akito, don't go overboard with rehearsing.
The air's really dry. You'll hurt your throat.

Stop making fake snow from crumbled styrofoam, Emu!
It's a pain to clean up.
My family takes extra care around this time of year not to get sick out of concern for Saki's well-being.

Hoo! Haa! I'll warm up by striking cool poses!
...It's not working.

Found you, my mascot buddy!
Aw, you're so warm and fluffy!

It's still not snowing!
I guess I'll have to make my own snow☆
Wouldn't it be the best thing ever to have a snowball fight in Phoenix Wonderland?

Robo-Nene gets so cold this time of year.
It's almost too cold to touch...
It's cold. I guess I have no choice but to play games inside.

Ah?! Oh, don't worry, I'm fine.
Just some static electricity.
Got to service all my robots and drones soon to start the new year on a good note!

Did you know you can grow snowflakes inside a bottle?
It's a cool experiment.

I came up with some winter-themed balloon art.
I should go show everyone right away.
Won't a steaming cup of instant noodles work just as well as a humidifier?
Temperature changes aren't good for computers, so I keep the A/C on all year round.

My eyes feel so dry...
I need my eyedrops...
Uh, where'd I put them?
The sound of an arrow subtly changes with each season.
It's good to see you're energetic, Otori, but don't run in the corridors.

Heating makes my skin so dry.
Does it bother you too, Kanade?
Festive illumination makes for an awesome selfie background.
I'm craving sweets, but Akito is at school, so I can't send him to buy me some...

Let's make this clear, Mizuki. I like cheesecake, but not cheese.
And that makes total sense!
It's too cold to get out of my cozy, warm bed.
Eating ice cream in my toasty room is a special winter pleasure.
It'd be nice to warm up with some hot soup, but I'd just burn my tongue.
Fiery, passionate songs will make you forget all about the cold!
Snow is unpleasant to touch but it's pretty to look at!

La la... La la la!
Won't someone sing with me?
The air is so clear in winter that meteor showers are easier to see.
It's a good idea to put some time into guitar maintenance when seasons change!
Besides uptempo songs, I should also try practicing winter ballads.
Singing on stage while it's snowing would be so dreamy!
The sea of glow sticks seen from stage is nearly as pretty as the starry sky!
I'll warm you up with my cheerful songs!
Street performances are a big effort in this weather.
Festive lights? Our SEKAI is already decorated with tons of vibrant graffiti.
There are many wonderful events in the winter.
KAITO, what do I need to do to make it snow?
It turns out soap bubbles aren't a good substitute for snow...

Yay! Emu said she'd show me real snow.
I can't wait!

I asked Mafuyu what it's like to feel cold, and she replied,
"It's like being in my world."

Everyone's asking me if I'm cold and is bringing me more clothes to put on.
What is this... feeling?

I get asked a lot if I'd feel cold without my socks.
But why?
It's me, deliveRIN good vibes no matter the weather!
Are festive lights made from real stars? No? Are you sure?
Wouldn't it be sweet if the white puffs of breath in winter were cotton candy?

Lovely scarf, KAITO!
Mind if I borrow this end?

Lights made from real stars?
Haha, you have a lively imagination!

That's a real long scarf, KAITO!
It's enough for you, me, Rin, and then some!
Singing clears away the winter gloom!
The crisp winter air makes me energized!
Does the warmth of our songs carry our voices high into the cold winter sky?
When it's cold, take it easy and keep warm!
What's your favorite hot drink when it's cold?

Heh, KAITO is sharing his scarf with Rin and Len.
What a heartwarming sight!
Rin, Len, and I looked like a strange creature when we were all sharing the same scarf!
Shorter days means longer nights and more stargazing!
Someone told me that eating ice cream by the heater is their favorite thing about winter.
The weather's got warmer, and lots of flowers are in bloom. I like spring!
I wonder if it's spring in Miku's world, too?

You're already thinking about summer, Saki?
You're so impatient.
This weather's perfect for a picnic under flowering cherry trees!
The best thing about spring is picnics among the flowers, with lots of yummy nibbles!

Uh... My nose feels weird!
Maybe it's hay fever? Atchoo!

It's laundry day today.
I'll air my bedding, too.

Dogs shed a lot of hair at this time of year.
You get a huge fur ball from brushing!
I'm a picnic lunch expert! You'll be amazed by the taste and presentation!

Spring's just another season.
I don't get why everyone makes such a fuss.
The problem with picnics under cherry blossoms is that it gets super crowded.
Nooo, the limited edition Phenny's coming out on a weekday when I have school.

Cherry blossom petals are so cute!
I'd love to have a cherry blossom costume.
Now it's gotten so warm, Samo has been shedding like crazy!
Eek! A caterpillar dropped right in front of my face!
It's still a bit chilly in the mornings, but it's good for jogging.
Oh, a patch of white clover! Let's see if I can find a four-leaf one!
The trouble with picnics is that you end up regretting having eaten so many sweets.
Spring flowers are nice, but seasonal spring sweets are better!

Cats come out to nap in parks on warm days.
I wish I weren't allergic to them!

Shizuku, don't wander off chasing flowers!
You'll get lost in the crowd!
Aah! It's the perfect day to sit in a sunny spot, and work on some embroidery!

Miku and Rin were so amazed by cherry blossoms.
I'll have to show them other flowers too!
I'd like to have a picnic but I could only go out in disguise...
Isn't it sad that the pretty cherry blossoms don't last long?
I'll have to take my camera when I go out for a walk and photograph some flowers!
It's so sunny, I think I'll go out for a walk while listening to some music!
I wonder if Kohane would be up for a picnic under the cherry blossoms?

"Please cooperate with the uniform inspection..."
Hmm... that didn't come out quite right...
The weather's great! We could sing outdoors for a change!
Warm and sunny weather makes me so sleepy in class...
Picnics? As long as they involve strawberry pancakes, I'm game.
Many people take up music in spring, but very few make a lifelong passion of it!
It's a lovely day for relaxing with a good book and a cup of coffee.

Shiraishi wants to have a picnic in the SEKAI.
Are there even flowers there?
Akito, have you prepared for the upcoming test?
I wonder what everyone thinks about doing a Spring-themed show?
Can't deny that flowers look pretty, but I bet they're hiding bugs...

Mmm... I feel warm and cozy.
I think I... am about to... fall asleep...

There's sunshine and there's flowers!
Why are we not having a picnic yet!?

Glorious sunshine!
No one will mind if I take a nap, right?

Spring has all sorts of good vibes!
It makes me extra cheerful and laid-back!

Nice weather draws out the crowds.
I'd rather stay home and play games.
Huh... Grapefruits are in season in spring, and they really do taste better!

A cherry petal?
It must have been carried here by the wind.
Now it's warmer, we can perform in the streets again.
I want to work a spring theme into our shows, but it can't be anything clichéd.

Spring vegetables are in season, huh.
I don't really care much for veggies.

Why's the noodle packaging pink?
Ah, right. It's a limited spring edition.

"Victory onion energizes the body!"
Interesting.
I'm not a fan of onions, though...

A cherry flower? Did the wind carry it here, or did
Ms. Mochizuki bring it?
My classmates talk about nothing but picnics.

Oh, the cherries are already shedding their blossoms.
It makes me feel a little sad.
Mizuki wants us to go on a picnic, but I don't know how to get Kanade on board.

A cherry blossom flavor drink?
I've got to try it!

There are lots of photogenic views in spring.
What to shoot after cherry blossoms?
Summer's just around the corner, and lots of new goodies come out then.
Pink is the color of spring, and pink's cute, so that makes spring cute too?

Photographing flowers?
Ena just wants flowers in her selfies' backgrounds.

Got to dress cute for spring!
Lots of styles work well in this season!

Are cherries in blossom yet?
I'd like to see them together with everyone!

The weather's really lovely.
It makes me want to sing outside!

Spring is a time of new beginnings.
And maybe also new song inspirations?
Ichika wants to have a picnic in my SEKAI, but it may not really be the best place.

Some stars can only be seen in the spring.
I'll ask Luka to help me find them.

Hmm, which spring song should I sing next?
They're all nice. I can't choose!
I think a costume inspired by cherry blossoms would be delightful.

Clover starts flowering in spring.
I love all the spring flowers!
Confetti looks even prettier when it glitters in the stage lights!
Len and Rin get hyped for spring, but then, they get excited for summer, too.

MEIKO's making us some sort of a strawberry dessert.
I bet it will be delicious!
Warm weather makes me space out, and time goes by before I know it!
Spring makes everyone happy, but what makes spring happy?

Welcome, Mr. Spring!
I'll make Mr. Spring smile too♪
Even when spring ends, flowers never wither here, and spring songs are always in season♪

Spring has come?
I'd love to see flowers in the real world.

Kanade showed me cherry blossoms...
They were very cute.

Mizuki gave me light pink ribbons.
I suppose I should try them on.
No one's a stranger to competitive cherry blossom catching, right?
Spring comes and goes, but don't let that make you sad!

Strawberry picking?
Don't pick on strawberries, you fruit bullies!

Rin, a cherry petal landed on your head.
Let me get it for you...
Which song did students graduating this spring sing at the ceremony?

Rin, you silly bean!
It means harvesting strawberries, not picking on them!
I hope my songs can inspire courage and motivation in this spring's graduates.

There's always a song on my lips in spring.
I can't stop myself!
Cherry blossoms look enchanting at night, in the pale light of the moon.

Some spring flowers are not only pretty, but also edible.
Try them!

La la la!
Guess what song that was!

Don't forget Mother's Day is in spring.
Tell your mom how much you love her!
Spring is a time of new beginnings. I hope I make a lot of new friends this year!

The flowers that make me think of spring are tulips.
Some grow them indoors.

It's easy to catch a cold when the seasons change.
Make sure to dress for the weather!

It's been a while since we last studied together at Saki's.
Oh... I wonder if I should bring my guitar.

Summer's a busy time!
There are festivals to go to, then there's the pool and the beach!

Summer homework?
Heh, I like to get it out of the way early so I can enjoy the holidays!

I'm a pretty good swimmer.
Saki and I used to go to the pool often.

Anyone else interested in astronomy?
The sky's crystal-clear in summer.

It's never too hot at Miku's SEKAI.
I wish we could do our rehearsals there all the time.
I don't mind just hanging out as long as we have enough time for practice.

It's been raining a lot...
Thankfully Miku let me practice over in SEKAI where I don't have to worry about the weather!

There's A/C and you can see all the fishes.

I mean, not counting the syrup...
No, I can't justify it like that.

Idols can't let themselves get sunburnt.
We have to take care of our complexion.

I need a new swimsuit.
Maybe this time I'll go for a bikini for a change.

Is shaved ice a Japanese thing, or is it Western?
It's delicious either way.
Some people get spicy food cravings in the summer, but that's a bit much for me...

Being able to practice in SEKAI is such a help.
It's nice there, and we don't have to worry about heatstroke.

It's too hot, I'm dying!
Kohane, let's get some ice cream!

The back alley's haunted?
You're pulling my leg.
N-No, I'm not scared!

The summer festival's coming up!
I won't be satisfied unless I'm on stage.
I like being on the soccer team, but it's tough playing outdoors in this heat.
Akito thinks game arcades are too noisy, but at least they have A/C on.
I used to love playing with sparklers with Saki and her friends.

Summer is a time for adventure!
Everyone who wants to join the Emu Expedition, gather ‘round!
Heat's bad for robots. Robo-Nene, here's a cold wet towel for you.
I feel like I'm going to end up baked to a crisp...
Sigh... I wonder who thought up the idea of giving out homework during summer vacations.

I'm not really affected by the summer heat...
Could it be because of my healthy diet?

Everyone else is sweating like mad.
Could it be that I'm more resilient towards changes in the weather?
Oh man, why can't the school be closed on rainy days?

Keeping up to date with the latest trends in cosmetics is important.
But doing so makes me want to buy all of it!

Akito, go buy me ice cream...
Hmph, he ran off again.
In this kind of weather, I can already picture Ena pestering her brother to buy her ice cream or something.

Yikes, what a downpour.
I hope it doesn't rain when I go shopping for fabrics.
There's plenty of songs suitable for singing on rainy days!
Don't forget to stay hydrated on hot days, even when you're out and about!
The girls have been coming to my world to take shelter from the rain lately.

I've started looking forward to rainy days.
That's when Minori's group comes to visit.

Rin has this idea to do a show on the beach.
I think it could be fun.

MEIKO hung a wind chime on the terrace.
Where did she find it...?
It never gets too hot in SEKAI. Poor Kohane, having to deal with the heat in hers!

Whew! Wearing a mascot costume is no joke!
It gets so hot and stuffy!

KAITO wants to light some fireworks.
Maybe we will! Heehee♪

I love summer ghost stories♪
Hmm... Wasn't there a haunted house somewhere in SEKAI?
I'm wild about summer fireworks, but sparklers are pretty fun, too!
I heard that eating shaved ice too fast will give you brain freeze. What's that like?

I wanna go to festivals, and watch fireworks, and go camping!
Summer's the best!
Summer homework should be just "Have fun!" or "Learn new songs!"
Rin wants to have a sparkler party night, so we're getting stuff ready.

The weather's really hot lately.
Make sure to take good care of yourself.
I want to sing along to the sound of waves, dancing together with the sea breeze.
What I like best about summer festivals is not the food or fireworks, but the music!

Anyone else want to come along?

Watch out for sudden thunderstorms!

Combat the hot weather with... ice cream!
It's not a good idea to eat too much, though.
Just hearing the gentle sound of a wind chimes makes me feel cooler, somehow?

I'm loving this weather.
Going for a swim in a river or the ocean would feel divine!

Competition for the yakisoba buns is wild at the canteen.
Did they improve the recipe?

The Gingko trees have turned yellow.
It's fall already.
Fall's a busy season, with school events and exams on top of that.

Did I finish the whole bag already?
My sweet cravings get out of control during fall.
There's a poem about maple leaves changing color out of loneliness.
That's very nice of you Tsukasa, but I'm warm enough without a coat or scarf.
When it comes to art, sure I can do music, but I'm terrible at drawing.
My dog brought me a pretty maple leaf when we were out on a walk. It was cute!
Yum! Apple pie tastes best in fall for some reason!

My other passions?
Well, I'm really into calligraphy.
Ramen is an awesome comfort food at this time of the year!

Honami's birthday is close to Halloween.
I think Saki is preparing something for both.

I ran into Haruka picking up acorns!
She says they remind her of penguins.

The seasonal fish are salmon and saury.
I'll make sure they feature in my menu.

Haruka saw me slip on dead leaves...
My behind hurts and so does my pride!
If I have to challenge myself in some way this fall, maybe something to do with sports?
I once recorded a music video where I was dancing on red maple leaves.

Aren't some acorns shaped a bit like penguins?
I collect those.
This fall I'm going to totally devote myself to singing and dancing, as usual!
Uh... I just remembered when I had to do sports on a variety show... Cringe!

Dad's making protein-rich lunches for my sister who's
going to compete in the Sports Festival.

Bookstores have special deals on right about now.
I'm going to stock up for the rest of the year!
I feel less sluggish now it's not so hot, so I can actually get things done.
I'm a little cold... Why won't Shiho ever come snuggle up with me?
Dad wants to take photos of the Gingko trees in the park with me next weekend.
I've got to study for exams...

Was that a cricket chirping?
In the middle of a busy town?

Hmm... I guess I could take up jogging.
Keeping fit helps with singing, too.
Kohane, want to grab some roasted sweet potatoes at my Dad's place?

It's so chilly!
I don't want to stand outside in the mornings...
Ena's panicking over having put on weight, but it's no surprise with her sweet tooth.
Do I like to read? Comics, yeah. But books put me to sleep after a couple pages.

You took this photo of the maple leaves, Kohane?
You really have a knack for photography.
I love to read, and long autumn evenings are perfect for it.
I mostly read mystery, but adventure novels are good once in a while, too.
Out of all events in fall, the sports ones I could do without.

Nooo! The last cookie I'd been saving is gone!
Did Saki get to it first?
